  <front>
   <head>SONG IV. The SKY-LARK.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">GO, tuneful bird, that glad'st the skies,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To Daphne's window speed thy way;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And there on quivering pinions rise,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And there thy vocal art display.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And if she deign thy notes to hear,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And if she praise thy matin song,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tell her the sounds that soothe her ear,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To Damon's native plains belong.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tell her, in livelier plumes array'd,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The bird from Indian groves may shine;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But ask the lovely partial maid,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">What are his notes compar'd to thine?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then bid her treat yon witless beau,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And all his flaunting race with scorn;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And lend an ear to Damon's woe,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who sings her praise, and sings forlorn.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
